{"lemma":"صِنْوٌ","slug":"صِنْوٌ","root":"ص.ن.#","root_slug":"ص-ن-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-ن-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25047"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B5%D9%90%D9%86%D9%92%D9%88%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"equivalent, equal duplicate, parallel, counterpart","examples":[{"text":"لَا صِنْوَ لَهُ","english":"unparalleled"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"equivalent, equal duplicate, parallel, counterpart; doublet"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"two or more branches or shrubs of a tree from the same root, or two or more trees derived from the same tree.","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"two or more branches or shrubs of a tree from the same root, or two or more trees derived from the same tree.; any branch or tree taken from a bigger tree.","tags":["broadly","obsolete"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"full-brother; (in the feminine) full-sister.","tags":["broadly","figuratively","obsolete"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"son","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"uncle","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"a type of hole dug in earth.","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/sˤinw/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25047","headword_ar":"صِنْوٌ","root":"Snw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One of a pair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, S, M, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of three,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of more than two,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of more than three,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of five,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of six,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) of palmtrees, (S, M, K,) or of any trees, (AHn, M, K,) or of trees resembling one another, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"growing from one root;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, S, M, K;) each [or every one] of such being called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sinow","text_ar":"صِنْو"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the other [or others growing with it]; (AHn, M;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SunowN","text_ar":"صُنْوٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) mentioned by Zj: (M:) two of such are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SinowaAni","text_ar":"صِنْوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SunowaAni","text_ar":"صُنْوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SanowaAni","text_ar":"صَنْوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which last implies that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SanowN","text_ar":"صَنْوٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SunowN","text_ar":"صُنْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SinowN","text_ar":"صِنْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SinoyaAni","text_ar":"صِنْيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SunoyaAni","text_ar":"صُنْيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SanoyaAni","text_ar":"صَنْيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which imply that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SinoYN","text_ar":"صِنْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SunoYN","text_ar":"صُنْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SanoYN","text_ar":"صَنْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are also dial. vars. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SinowN","text_ar":"صِنْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SunowN","text_ar":"صُنْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SanowN","text_ar":"صَنْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] (K;) and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SinowaAnN","text_ar":"صِنْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, M) and [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSonaA='N","text_ar":"اَصْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) the former pl. differing from the first of the duals mentioned above by being perfectly decl. (AZ, S, * TA.) Hence, in the Kur [xiii. 4],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SinowaAnK wagayorui SinowaAnK","text_ar":"صِنْوَانٍ وَغَيْرُِ صِنْوَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) i. e. Palmtrees"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having one root and"},{"kind":"text","text":"[others]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having distinct roots:"},{"kind":"text","text":"Hafs read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SunowaAn","text_ar":"صُنْوَان"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qunowaAn","text_ar":"قُنْوَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qinowN","text_ar":"قِنْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; of the dial. of Temeem. (Bd.) ―         -b2-  And hence, (TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A brother;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but not so called unless coupled with another: (Sh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a brother by the same father:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a brother by the same mother;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is indicated by an explanation of one of the pls in what follows:] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a brother such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$qiyq","text_ar":"شقِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the father and mother:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$q","text_ar":"شق"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a son;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) because he has branched forth from one stock [with his father]: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a paternal uncle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) but this last meaning is taken from a trad. cited in what follows: (TA:) the fem. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSonaA='N","text_ar":"اَصْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SinowaAnN","text_ar":"صِنْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as above]. (M, K.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~u Alr~ajuli Sinowu A^abiyhi","text_ar":"عَمُّ الرَّجُلِ صِنْوُ اَبِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The paternal uncle of the man is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sinow","text_ar":"صِنْو"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of his father"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T, S;) meaning that the stock of both is one. (T, TA.) [And it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SanowaAnN wgayoru SinowaAnK","text_ar":"صَنْوَانٌ وغَيْرُ صِنْوَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", relating to a man's children, means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sons of one mother by different fathers, and children of different mothers by one father."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 608.) ―         -b3-  [Hence the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSonaA='N","text_ar":"اَصْنَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Likes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fellows."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiy~ataAni SinowaAni","text_ar":"رَكِيَّتَانِ صِنْوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two wells near together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, M, K, TA,) or (so in the TA and in some copies of the K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that yield water from one spring."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, K, TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SinowN","text_ar":"صِنْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A widened well"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafarN","text_ar":"حَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from which water is not drawn and of the water of which no use is made:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-Buzurj, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SinowaAnN","text_ar":"صِنْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn-Buzurj, TA.) ―         -b6-  See also what follows."}],"source_refs":["AHn","S","M","K","TA","AZ","Sh","Az"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}